<h3 class="mt-5">📊 Logical Data Model</h3>
<p>This data model captures the structure of EventNest and how different entities are related. It demonstrates two key one-to-many relationships:</p>
 
<ul>
    <li><strong>Event → Booking</strong>: One event can have multiple ticket bookings</li>
    <li><strong>Event → Review</strong>: One event can have multiple user reviews</li>
</ul>
 
<p>The main entities and attributes are:</p>
 
<h5 class="mt-3">🗂 Event</h5>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Id (PK)</strong> – Unique identifier for the event</li>
    <li>Title – Name of the event</li>
    <li>Date – Scheduled date of the event</li>
    <li>Location – Venue or city</li>
    <li>Price – Ticket price per seat</li>
    <li>ImageUrl – URL or path to the event poster image</li>
</ul>
 
<h5 class="mt-3">🎟 Booking</h5>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Id (PK)</strong> – Unique booking identifier</li>
    <li><strong>EventId (FK)</strong> – Refers to the booked event</li>
    <li>UserName – Name of the user who booked</li>
    <li>Seats – Number of seats booked</li>
</ul>
 
<h5 class="mt-3">⭐ Review</h5>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Id (PK)</strong> – Unique review identifier</li>
    <li><strong>EventId (FK)</strong> – Refers to the reviewed event</li>
    <li>Rating – Numeric rating (e.g., 1–5)</li>
    <li>Comment – Text review by the user</li>
</ul>
 
